notesStmt.note: Incipit: Omnem scientiam et disciplinam sacra scriptura transcendit (f. 1r).

msContents.summary: Verse summary of St. Raymundus de Peñaforte's Summa, with extensive anonymous commentary.

supportDesc.extent: 175 leaves : 289 x 209 (243 x 155) mm. bound to 305 x 212 mm
supportDesc.foliation: i + 175 + i; [1-175], modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 2 columns of 44-46 lines; ruled in ink.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a Gothic cursive script in the hand of Johannes Kemp[?] (f. 173v). Same scribe as that of Ms. Codex 731.

decoDesc.decoNote: Initials in red, green and yellow, some with faces (f. 2r, 4r, 6v, 42r, 49r, 53r, 73v, 76v, 111v, 119r, 129r, 133r, 138v, 141r, 143r, 147r, 149v, 150r, 151r, 153r, 154v, 157r, 164r, 166r); rubricated throughout.
Decorated initial, Initial Q, Faces, f. 150r
Decorated initial, Initial C, Faces, f. 164r
Decorated initial, Initial P, Face, f. 166r

binding.p: Contemporary blind-stamped sheepskin over wooden boards, rebacked, new guards.

origin.p: Written in southern Germany or Austria (Zacour-Hirsch) in 1422 (f. 173v).

history.provenance: Sold by Charles W. Traylen (Guildford, England), 1962.
